text.section:
A court of competent jurisdiction of this State shall give prompt consideration to a petition for injunctive relief and may enjoin, temporarily or permanently, the licensor from exercising electronic self-help even if authorized by a license term or enjoin the licensee from misappropriation or misuse of computer information, as may be appropriate, upon consideration of the following:
Grave harm of the kinds stated in subsection (h) of this section, or the threat thereof, whether or not the licensor has reason to know of those circumstances;
Irreparable harm or threat of irreparable harm to the licensee or licensor;
That the party seeking the relief is more likely than not to succeed under its claim when it is finally adjudicated;
That all of the conditions to entitle a person to the relief under the laws of this State have been fulfilled; and
That the party that may be adversely affected is adequately protected against loss, including a loss because of misappropriation or misuse of computer information, that it may suffer because the relief is granted under this title.
